Check this out, they say that current implementation of async/await overuses exceptions. Well, consider this!

```python
async def mul(numbers, control, out):
    multiplier = 2
    while True:
        try:
            await select([numbers, control], [])
        except ChannelClosed:
            out.close()
            return
        except numbers.received as value:
            await out.put(value * multiplier)
        except control.received as new_mult:
            multiplier = new_mul
```

