It you add rows faster than the animation time, the animation is reset when the rows are re-appended to the table after sorting. I think the easiest solution would be to add a separate timer for each highlight and then remove the pulse animation in the callback... e.g.

```js
$row.addClass('pulse');
setTimeout(function(){
  $row.removeClass('pulse');
}, 3000);
```

It's not as nice as having the animation with a built-in timer, but it'll be more consistent.

