@over64 (@tagliala) I don't know too much about `bower-installer` but after taking a look at its github page and some of the issues.  I believe the issue isn't with `Font-Awesome`, but with how you have `bower-installer` configured.  

As you see the Font-Awesome.css is looking for the fonts in the path `../fonts/fontawesome-webfont` which doesn't match the structure that your `bower-installer` paths is setup.  You have everything being installed in the one directory and not in its specific subfolders.  Looking at the docs, you probably want something for paths like the following:

```json
"install" : {
    "path" : {
      "css": "src/css",
      "js": "src/js",
      "eot": "src/fonts",
      "svg": "src/fonts",
      "ttf": "src/fonts",
      "woff": "src/fonts",
      "woff2": "src/fonts",
      "/[sc|le]ss$/": "src/css"
    },
    "sources" : {
      ...
    }
}
```

From what i can tell from `bower-installer` is that one of the major issues is that the file paths defined by the bower component must match the same file structure that you store the files in.  You cant "flatten" the component and toss everything into a single folder as those files will have no idea how to reference each other.  

I would say that if you are still having issues with this that you should probably create an issue for `bower-installer`. The file structure for `Font-Awesome` appears to be the correct (or rather most commonly used) structure.

