@nunoplopes I'm currently building an experimental solver on top of Z3 that uses an incomplete method that can only prove sat. As such I wanted to use as many cheap pre-processing steps as possible so that I can determine a query is unsat in fairly trivial cases.

There isn't any detailed documentation on what each tactic does or what their complexity is so I resorted to looking at the list of available tactics and trying out tactics that sounded helpful based on their name. The `propagate-bv-bounds` tactic sounded like it would simplify contradictory bounds to false. My initial experimentation showed that it could do this but these were on small examples. I only recently started trying on much larger examples and ran into performance problems.

For now I've stopped using this tactic. If I get time I'll implement my own approach that just looks for very simple contradictory bounds which is all I wanted to do.

